text: Zell im Wiesental is a town in Lörrach in Baden-Württemberg, Germany. It is in the Black Forest, on the river Wiese, 26 km northeast of Basel, and 32 km south of Freiburg. The town is known for being the birthplace of Constanze Weber, wife of Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart. == Gallery == File:Zell im Wiesental, straatzicht met katholische Stadtpfarrkirche foto3 2013-07-26 13.00.jpg|Zell im Wiesental, church (Stadtpfarrkirche) in the street File:Mambach, geit met Maria Frieden Kapelle foto1 2013-07-26 12.27.jpg|Mambach, goat with chapel (die Maria Frieden Kapelle) File:Atzenbach, straatzicht foto1 2013-07-26 12.46.jpg|Atzenbach, view to a street File:Silbersau, wegpanorama foto4 2013-07-26 12.06.jpg|Silbersau, road panorama == References == Category:Lörrach (district)
